The [2 carat emerald cut diamond](/2-carat-emerald-cut-diamond) has two price tags separated by $19,672. In natural diamonds, a GIA-certified F-VS1 at 2ct costs [$24,407](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/14013191?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). In lab-grown, an IGI-certified D-FL — better color, better clarity, same 2ct — costs [$4,735](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28828463?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Same carat weight. Same step-cut facets. The same 9mm × 7mm face-up size on the hand. Five times the price difference.

This page answers every question the "how much is a 2 carat emerald cut diamond" buyer needs before spending that money. It covers what a 2ct emerald cut actually looks like — dimensions and face-up presence — why the step-cut shape demands stricter clarity standards than any brilliant cut, the full natural and lab price tables from current certified market data, and how 2.5ct compares for buyers considering the step up.

This page is about the diamond. Ring settings are a separate decision. If you want setting options for a 2ct emerald cut, see [emerald cut diamond ring settings](/emerald-cut-diamond-ring-settings). This page covers the stone.

---

**TL;DR**

- Natural 2ct emerald cut: [GIA 2.00ct F-VS1 Ideal Cut at **$24,407**](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/14013191?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
- Lab 2ct emerald cut: [IGI 2.00ct D-FL Ideal Cut at **$4,735**](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28828463?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
- Size: approximately 9mm long × 7mm wide — the full hall-of-mirrors effect is visible at this size
- Clarity minimum: VS2 for natural (SI1 shows face-up in step-cut); in lab, D-FL is accessible at $4,735
- Color minimum: G in white gold/platinum, H acceptable in yellow gold
- 2.5ct natural: [GIA 2.52ct D-VVS2 at $31,566](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29142058?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

→ Best value at 2ct: [IGI 2.00ct D-FL lab emerald cut at **$4,735**](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28828463?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). D-FL in a natural 2ct would cost over $60,000. In lab, it is the entry price for exactly 2ct.

Priority: if you are choosing between natural and lab at 2ct, the grade inversion makes lab the stronger value on every measurable criterion except natural origin.

---

## 2 Carat Emerald Cut Diamond Price

The question "how much does a 2 carat emerald cut diamond cost" has a complicated answer in natural diamonds. The emerald cut is a step-cut shape. Its wide, open rectangular facets expose inclusions that brilliant cuts hide behind 57 tiny scattering facets. That forces buyers into VS2 or VS1 clarity to get an eye-clean stone. GIA certification at that quality level at 2ct is expensive and the selection is thin.

Current certified market inventory shows one natural GIA-certified 2ct emerald cut: [GIA 2.00 Carat F-VS1 Ideal Cut at $24,407](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/14013191?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). F color is near-colorless. VS1 is comfortably eye-clean in a 2ct emerald cut. This is what a correctly-graded, GIA-certified natural 2ct emerald cut costs.

To understand that price in context, here is the natural emerald cut price progression from 1ct to 2.5ct across certified market data:

