The price jump from 1.5ct to 2ct is not linear. Between a 1.5ct E-VS1 at $10,409 and a 2ct F-VS1 at $24,407, the price more than doubles. This is the carat weight premium — natural diamonds price exponentially as weight increases, not proportionally. A 2ct emerald cut does not cost twice the price of a 1ct. It costs four to eight times as much, depending on grades.

The emerald cut's step-cut shape adds a second premium on top of carat weight: the clarity premium. VS1 at 2ct in a step-cut stone costs significantly more than VS2, and SI1 is generally not an option. These two compounding premiums explain why the natural 2ct market sits at $24,000 for a single GIA-certified stone.

