    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>H-I / SI1</td>
      <td>Rarely</td>
      <td>Yellow gold only</td>
      <td>Not recommended at 2ct; inclusions frequently visible face-up</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

The clarity tax is why natural 2ct emerald cuts are so expensive. The shape forces VS1 or better, and VS1 at 2ct in natural carries a significant price premium. In lab diamonds, the clarity tax disappears — VS1, VVS1, and FL all exist at prices under $5,500 for 2ct. You do not compromise on clarity in lab at this size.

