The range from $2,229 to $5,335 for near-2ct lab emerald cuts covers a significant spread in carat and grade. The [$2,229 IGI F-VVS1 at 1.94ct](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29147824?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the entry price for near-2ct lab in a clean grade. The [$4,735 IGI D-FL at exactly 2.00ct](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28828463?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the recommended starting point for buyers who want exactly 2ct on the certificate.

Between those two: the 0.06ct difference between 1.94ct and 2.00ct is not visible on the hand without a measuring device. If "2.00" on the certificate matters to you, pay the $4,735. If you are buying the face-up look and size, the 1.94ct F-VVS1 at $2,229 leaves $2,506 more available for a ring setting.

