## 2.5 Carat Emerald Cut Diamond

If your budget extends above the 2ct natural range, two GIA-certified natural emerald cut diamonds are available near 2.5ct in certified market inventory.

The [GIA 2.52ct D-VVS2 Ideal Cut at $31,566](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29142058?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the better value at this size. D color and VVS2 clarity — both better grades than the 2ct F-VS1 — and the size jumps to approximately 9.8mm × 7.6mm. The $7,159 premium over the 2ct natural buys a visible size increase and better grades across the board.

The [GIA 2.55ct G-VVS2 Ideal Cut at $35,178](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23683538?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the larger stone but at G color — warm metal settings handle this stone better than white gold. The $3,612 gap between the two 2.5ct stones is accounted for largely by the D vs G color difference at that carat weight. At 2.5ct in white gold, D-VVS2 is the right choice.

